movie_title: Star Wars: Episode I - The Phantom Menace
title: mediocrity
review: At it finest, Episode One is merely an average movie.  Yes, loaded with extravagant special effects, but movies worthy of such hype shouldn't depend on those effects to hold the audience.  With no actual plot other than 'how will they make it', the movie becomes the theatrical equivalent of a bad parade.And don't get me started on Jar Jar.
